--------------------------------------------------------------------
Significant modifications from the original work
--------------------------------------------------------------------

- Replaced LangGraph-based orchestration with Claude Code sub-agent
  dispatch (the Task tool), so the pipeline runs natively inside the
  Claude Code CLI without an external graph framework.
- Removed external LLM provider dependencies (OpenAI, Anthropic API,
  Google, xAI, DeepSeek, Qwen, GLM, MiniMax, OpenRouter, Ollama, etc.).
  The system now runs entirely on the user's Claude Code subscription;
  no separate LLM API key is required.
- Reimplemented agent definitions as Claude Code agent markdown files
  under `agents/`.
- Added bilingual (Korean / English) HTML and Markdown report
  rendering via `tools/render_html.py` and `tools/render_md.py`,
  switchable through the `--lang` flag.
- Replaced FinnHub / Tushare / paid news data sources with yfinance
  (price, technicals, news, fundamentals), Reddit, and StockTwits.
- Repackaged as a Claude Code plugin with a `/ticker` slash-command
  skill at `.claude/skills/ticker/SKILL.md`.

